# Python Package Structure

## Layout per module (hexagonal)

```
packages/module-{name}/
└── module_{name}/
    ├── api.py          # facade — sole cross-module entry point
    ├── register.py     # register_services(registry)
    ├── routes/         # HTTP driving adapter
    ├── ports/          # Protocol interfaces
    ├── services/       # use cases; depend on ports, not adapters
    ├── adapters/       # port implementations
    ├── schemas/        # Pydantic DTOs
    └── tasks.py        # Celery (worker modules)
```

## Naming

- Package: `module-platform`, import: `module_platform`
- Services: `{Domain}Service`, `{Action}Orchestrator` (e.g. `SyncOrchestrator`)
- Facades: `{Domain}Module` (e.g. `DocumentsModule`)
- Celery tasks: verb + object (`sync_case_from_dms`, `ingest_document`)
- Enums: in `cortex_core.enums`, not in modules

## Layering

```
routes/  →  api.py  →  services/  →  ports/  ←  adapters/
```

## Shared libs

| Lib | Contents |
|-----|----------|
| `cortex-models` | SQLAlchemy ORM, `get_db`, session factory |
| `cortex-core` | ports, enums, settings, Celery, SearchPort |
| `cortex-connectors` | Alfresco, Blob, OCR adapters |
| `cortex-observability` | metrics/tracing — no business logic |

No ORM in `cortex-core`. No use-cases in libs.

## Style

- Python 3.12+, type hints on public methods
- Pydantic v2: `model_config = {"from_attributes": True}` for ORM mapping
- Async only where I/O requires it; Celery tasks may be sync

